Form Element - Hidden Form Field - cml:hidden

- Renders a hidden form input
- Accepts all Common Attributes

The following CML will output "true" in a column called "secret_sauce":

[code] <cml:hidden name="secret_sauce" value="true" /> [/code]

This is best used for submitting additional hidden information, such as the contributor's browser information with the [code]user_agent[/code] validator:

[code] <cml:hidden label="contributors_browser" validates="user_agent" /> [/code]